Beam current was in the range 10-40 Na.
Fifteen Si detectors are placed at backward
angles, from 100 to 170 degrees in step of 5 degrees;
they are cooled via a cold finger kept at liquid
nitrogen temperature.
The targets used were thin self-supporting natural
carbon foils, ~13 mu-gr/cm**2 for the measurements
from 350 to 700 keV and ~50 mu-gr/cm**2 above 700 KeV.
The target tilting angle was 20 degrees.
Corrected data are received from M. Chiari,
Last checking has been done.
